</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Loosen the 2 screws [A]. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-F3590D6A-CC31-47CB-A6BF-DD9178698D5A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-738EC6FD-D52F-44D0-9A3E-EA80C5C73604-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-738EC6FD-D52F-44D0-9A3E-EA80C5C73604-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 2 screws of the switch and leave the switch connected to the wires. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><draft-comment translate="no" class="- topic/draft-comment ">---Nieuwe foto is nu zwart---</draft-comment> 
</p><fig id="GUID-03BAFE20-2668-4110-80BC-9301DD84B40D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-3332C000-89A1-4047-B281-280EF07120EE-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-3332C000-89A1-4047-B281-280EF07120EE-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-F8704ACD-92ED-492F-A50D-A4A42ECBC5FE" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Step 1: How to adjust the magnet bracket</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-1B05A219-7687-4728-B209-873BFDFE0EA5" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Close the top cover. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure that magnet [B] touches the bracket [C]. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-C6D8DFF2-FE3E-471A-835C-65702C44C2F4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-738EC6FD-D52F-44D0-9A3E-EA80C5C73604-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-738EC6FD-D52F-44D0-9A3E-EA80C5C73604-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Push up the bracket [C] till you have no play in the magnet pins [D] . 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Do not put force on the top cover. it should stay in the natural position. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">A gap between the top cover [A] and the rubber stop [B] is allowed. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-398EB12E-A684-47F8-9928-C1A3AD0339F4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-70AD0918-8E3F-4C09-BDF1-CA1B6C745010-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-70AD0918-8E3F-4C09-BDF1-CA1B6C745010-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-6BA7219A-4FFB-420E-95B7-F2D5E1B99140" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C906BCC0-D882-4BB9-9806-5D858510BA6A-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C906BCC0-D882-4BB9-9806-5D858510BA6A-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Push the bracket [C] upwards and lock the 2 screws [A] trough the maintenance door. 
